22 WHEREAS, Kevin Kresse is a Little Rock native and full-time sculptor
23 and painter who was awarded the commission to create the bronze statue of
24 Johnny Cash that now resides in the National Statuary Hall Collection in the
25 United States Capitol; and
26
27 WHEREAS, Kevin Kresse was born and raised in North Little Rock,
28 attended Catholic High School for Boys and the University of Arkansas at
29 Little Rock, and continues to live in central Arkansas; and
30
31 WHEREAS, Kevin Kresse's sculpture of Johnny Cash is one (1) of two (2)
32 sculptures that now represent Arkansas in the capital city of the United
33 States; and
34
35 WHEREAS, Kevin Kresse was the tenth of eleven (11) children born to
36 parents whom he remembers as excelling at making and fixing things by hand;
